metadata.name: Tally! #7293
metadata.description:
Tally! Is a year long, free, open edition to celebrate fxhash v2. Data from the minting of Tally! will be used to create other new artworks.

This artwork is simply about counting up from one to wherever we end up, with a litle bit of Fizz Buzz thrown in. Mints that have a prime numbers* as factors will have slight variations. Sometimes those variations will combine, sometimes you have to get to really high numbers for multiple prime numbers to combine.

Where the finally Tally! ends up who knows? But there's going to be a lot of tallying along the way, and it'll give you something to do while waiting between other mints.

INSTRUCTIONS ::

'?forceWidth=xxxx' on the end of the URL to change the width of the image
's' = save image

metadata.name: 99 recorridos #5
Entangled #216
metadata.description:
Entangled is a cross-chain, generative art project developed as a series of particle simulations that interact with each other in various ways across separate blockchains and browser windows. Inspired by the phenomenon of quantum entanglement, this project aims to connect two, often separate, parts of the generative art community by directly linking them together.
 
Entangled features two distinct on-chain NFT collections residing on the Ethereum and Tezos blockchains. These collections are connected through shared interactions in real-time, using cross-chain and local storage technologies to enable a system whereby particles in separate browser instances respond to and mirror each other.

The series consist of a total of 512 unique editions (256 on each blockchain) that are randomly paired with a corresponding iteration on the other. When two or more instances are opened in separate browser windows they will start to interact in different ways depending on whether they are paired or not, or if an entangled pair is owned by the same collector.

metadata.name: Morixels Mega Colab #2 #85
(fx)moji #124
metadata.description:
Emoji is the word for visual language, a way to express emotion without words.

From its humble origins as a Japanese emoticon in the mid-1990s, they exploded in popularity when appeared as a critical part of Apple's iPhone launch in 2007. The internationalization of emoji is an inexorable force, and today it is almost impossible to send a message without using one.

Emojis evolved as a way to communicate quickly and easily, and now they will evolve one more time and become an NFT generative art reborn as (fx)moji where basic geometric forms create a new full set of emojis expressions.

32 emojis,
7 Animations,
6 Color &
Infinite expressions 😊

Made with love ❤️ 🧡 💛 💚 💙 and p5js

metadata.name: Annum #7436
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Urban Flow Scribe – Free Edition #15
metadata.description:
Urban Flow Scribe – Free Edition is a preview of the final algorithm.

Urban Flow Scribe is a generative art project that fuses the raw energy of street art with the fluidity of asemic writing. Each stroke emerges from the oscillating harmony of sine and cosine waves, creating dynamic, abstract compositions that echo the chaotic rhythm of urban expression.

Everything is generated with code.
This work uses p5.js library.

metadata.name: Pumpkin Head #41
metadata.description: The creatures observed within the desolate cemetery of the city are commonly known as "pumpkin heads." According to local accounts, these entities are believed to be the most horrifying creatures in the entire city, instilling sheer terror in those who encounter them. It is rumored that the mere sound of their voices has the power to awaken the dormant zombies, causing them to rise from their graves once again.

metadata.name: Flux Mesh #1
metadata.description:
This is my take on 3D simplex noise. Time is a dimension here.

Square size and color are determined by noise value over time.

Each NFT iteration has randomized color scheme, grid size, and noise zoom.
